INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'c501c31e-c087-4b04-9b27-426300edf8a0',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Fastify Security Hardening — CORS, Rate Limiting, Headers, and Injection Defense$escape$,
  $escape$Fastify's plugin ecosystem handles the full security surface out of the box. Register `@fastify/helmet` to set secure HTTP headers (CSP, HSTS, X-Frame-Options) in one call. For CORS, `@fastify/cors` lets you whitelist origins per-route or globally — avoid `origin: true` in production. Rate limiting via `@fastify/rate-limit` operates on the raw request level with Redis-backed storage for distributed deployments; set `max` and `timeWindow` per route using `config.rateLimit` in route options for fine-grained control. For injection prevention, never interpolate request params into raw SQL — use `@fastify/postgres` with parameterized queries (`$1, $2` placeholders). Fastify's schema-based validation via JSON Schema (the `schema.body`, `schema.querystring`, `schema.params` route options) is your first injection firewall: unknown properties are stripped by default because `additionalProperties` resolves to false when using `ajv-type-provider-typebox`. Always define strict schemas — it's not optional hygiene, it's load-bearing security.$escape$,
  $escape$import Fastify from 'fastify'
import helmet from '@fastify/helmet'
import cors from '@fastify/cors'
import rateLimit from '@fastify/rate-limit'

const app = Fastify()

await app.register(helmet)
await app.register(cors, { origin: ['https://app.yourdomain.com'] })
await app.register(rateLimit, { max: 100, timeWindow: '1 minute' })

app.post('/search', {
  config: { rateLimit: { max: 20, timeWindow: '1 minute' } },
  schema: {
    body: { type: 'object', properties: { q: { type: 'string', maxLength: 200 } }, required: ['q'], additionalProperties: false }
  },
  handler: async (req) => ({ query: req.body.q })
})$escape$,
  $escape$typescript$escape$,
